{"questionId":"9074257","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A longitudinal wave travels in a medium with speed 340 m s<sup>−1</sup>. The graph shows the variation&nbsp;with time <em>t</em> of the displacement <em>x</em> of a particle P in the medium. Positive displacements on&nbsp;the graph correspond to displacements to the right for particle P.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/169e59fd38166feff85b08150e1312293757ae08.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Another wave travels in the medium. The graph shows the variation with time <em>t</em> of the&nbsp;displacement of each wave at the position of P.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/cc8e58e90c2fb27c247f44695270e168245fa218.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>State the phase difference between the two waves.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>«±»&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>/</mo><mn>90</mn><mo>°</mo></math>&nbsp; <em><strong>OR</strong></em>&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>/</mo><mn>270</mn><mo>°</mo></math>&nbsp;✓</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9074257","referenceCode":"21N.2.SL.TZ0.3b.i","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"State the phase difference between the two waves.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 4: Waves","4.1 – Oscillations","Core","Topic 4: Waves"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}